# TypeScript Conventions

- Strict mode enabled — no `any` unless truly unavoidable
- Shared types live in `src/types/index.ts` — import from `@/types`
- API request/response pairs follow `{Action}Request` / `{Action}Response` naming
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases
- Contentstack API types use `snake_case` field names to match their API
- App-domain types use `camelCase`
- Every API route handler should type-annotate its parsed body: `const body = (await req.json()) as MyRequest`
